SIMPLE: granary
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Granary
<hw>Gran"a*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Granaries</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. <ets>granarium</ets>,
fr. <ets>granum</ets> grain. See <er>Garner</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A storehouse or repository for grain, esp. after it is thrashed or
husked; a cornhouse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> (<mark>Fig</mark>.), <def>A
region fertile in grain; in this sense, equivalent to
<altname>breadbasket</altname>, used figuratively; <as>as, Ukraine, the
<ex>granary</ex> of the Soviet Union</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q>The exhaustless <qex>granary</qex> of a world.</q>
<rj><qau>Thomson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Granate</ent>⟦br⟧
